  "subtopic": "Practice Problem 25.4",
  "question": "If the cumulative distribution function is given by $F(x) = \\begin{cases} 0 & x < 0 \\\\ \\frac{1}{2} & 0\\le x < 1 \\\\ \\frac{3}{5} & 1\\le x < 2 \\\\ \\frac{4}{5} & 2\\le x < 3 \\\\ \\frac{9}{10} & 3\\le x < 3.5 \\\\ 1 & 3.5\\le x \\end{cases}$ Calculate the probability mass function.",
  "answer": "$\\Pr(X = 0) = F(0) = \\frac{1}{2}$, $\\Pr(X = 1) = F(1)-F(1^-) = \\frac{3}{5} - \\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{1}{10}$, $\\Pr(X = 2) = F(2)-F(2^-) = \\frac{4}{5} - \\frac{3}{5} = \\frac{1}{5}$, $\\Pr(X = 3) = F(3)-F(3^-) = \\frac{9}{10} - \\frac{4}{5} = \\frac{1}{10}$, $\\Pr(X = 3.5) = F(3.5)-F(3.5^-) = 1 - \\frac{9}{10} = \\frac{1}{10}$ and 0 otherwise.",
  "explanation": "Answer: $\\Pr(X = 0) = F(0) = \\frac{1}{2}$, $\\Pr(X = 1) = F(1)-F(1^-) = \\frac{3}{5} - \\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{1}{10}$, $\\Pr(X = 2) = F(2)-F(2^-) = \\frac{4}{5} - \\frac{3}{5} = \\frac{1}{5}$, $\\Pr(X = 3) = F(3)-F(3^-) = \\frac{9}{10} - \\frac{4}{5} = \\frac{1}{10}$, $\\Pr(X = 3.5) = F(3.5)-F(3.5^-) = 1 - \\frac{9}{10} = \\frac{1}{10}$ and 0 otherwise.",
  "source": "Finan §25 — Practice Problem 25.4"
